{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e051d836-7abf-443e-8ed1-5c5dfee4940a","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed **above** them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing by reordering:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_piaE8VrxzvMTGGtFRyBoLi","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-f3496ce53d744234b2954319ee805fe2/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-f3496ce53d744234b2954319ee805fe2/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"141cb744-592b-4dbb-9bdc-97a78172736c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear **before** them in the compilation order.\n\nIn the `.fsproj`, the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — references `BrokenOrder.Domain` (from `Domain.fs`)\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines the domain types\n3. `Program.fs` — references both\n\n`Services.fs` is compiled first but it depends on `Domain.fs` which comes after it. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs` (defines types)\n2. `Services.fs` (uses Domain types)\n\n\n3. `Program.fs` (depends on both)","outputTokens":417,"requestId":"190B:287A16:1338F10:1598F4A:6A066F01"},"id":"6916d726-437a-48f1-9559-4f4a2f4dd67c","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:55:36.988Z","parentId":"8ce6c426-a8ae-4530-91dd-91e2b50c2af0"}
